The infant’s body was discovered under a bridge in an informal area on Sunday. CAPE TOWN - The body of a newborn baby has been found in Langa, in Cape Town. The infant’s body was discovered under a bridge in an informal area on Sunday. Police officials were on scene when forensic pathologists removed the body from the scene. The police’s Noloyiso Rwexana said: “Langa police are investigating following the discovery of a newborn baby. The circumstances are under investigation.”